The paper discusses security issues in the authentication mechanism used in LTE, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the use of public key cryptography and key management, which are relevant to network security (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed IPG-AKA protocol involves the use of a console grid, which could be related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) or information theory (cs.IT).
